<h2>🏝 Islands & Environment</h2>

<p>
Most islands are very low-lying coral atolls, often only a few meters above sea level. The country is highly vulnerable to climate change and rising sea levels.
</p>

<p>
Its marine environment includes coral reefs, tropical fish species, and large lagoon systems that support fishing and biodiversity.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🌦 Climate</h2>

<p>
The climate is tropical, with hot temperatures and high humidity throughout the year. Rainfall is frequent, and the islands are occasionally affected by storms and typhoons.
</p>

